.setup b2hsetup
:appendix.
.*--------------------
:h1 id=taglist.Symbols, control words, macros and tags supported by &sysname
.*-----
:h2.&amp.Symbols
:p.There are literally hundreds of &script., GML and &bm. symbols
and over 300 are defined to &sysname..  All ISO 8859-1 characters
are defined plus many other &bm. symbols, so files written in
languages other than English should display correctly if the proper
&amp.symbols are used (e.g. &amp.Aumlaut for &Aumlaut., &amp.eacute
for &eacute.). In addition, the symbols used by XEDITG and CHARGES
line-drawing tools are also defined.
:p.If you need a special symbol which is not currently supported,
simply define it in a user symbol table and point &sysname. to it
using the :xph.USERSYM=:exph. option.
:table cols='3* 2* 3* 2* 3* 2*'
       align='l c l c l c'
       split=yes.
:tcap.Supported &amp.symbols
:tdesc.Some symbols appear correctly only when viewed using a WEB
browser.
:etdesc.
:thd.
:c.Symbol:c.Value
:c.Symbol:c.Value
:c.Symbol:c.Value
:ethd.
