:rev refid=r46.
:h2 id=syssym.System &amp.Symbols
:p.The following :q.system-type:eq. symbols, set by Script/VS, GML
and Bookmaster, are also set by &sysname. to allow user-written
macros and other markup to execute under &sysname. without
modification as much as possible.
:tdef  id=syssym
       cols='*'
       hp='3'.
:table cols='* 2* 2*'
       align='l'
       valign='t'
       split=yes.
:tcap.System &amp.symbols
:thd.
:c.Symbol
:c.Description
:c.Value
:ethd.
:row refid=syssym temp.
:c.Date and Time
:row.
:c.:xph.&amp.SYSYEAR:exph.
:c.Year of the century
:c.00-99
:row.
:c.:xph.&amp.SYSMONTH:exph.
:c.Month of the year
:c.01-12
:row.
:c.:xph.&amp.SYSDAYOFM:exph.
:c.Day of the month
:c.01-31
:row.
:c.:xph.&amp.SYSDAYOFW:exph.
:c.Day of the week
:c.1-7 ("1" is Sunday)
:row.
:c.:xph.&amp.SYSDAYOFY:exph.
:c.Day of the year
:c.001-366
:row.
:c.:xph.&amp.SYSHOUR:exph.
:c.Hour of the day
:c.00-23
:row.
:c.:xph.&amp.SYSMINUTE:exph.
:c.Minute of the hour
:c.00-59
:row.
:c.:xph.&amp.SYSSECOND:exph.
:c.Second of the minute
:c.00-59
:row.
:c.:xph.&amp.$YEAR:exph.
:c.Four-digit year
:c.:pv.yyyy:epv.
:row refid=syssym temp.
:c.Output Device Characteristics
:row.
:c.:xph.&amp.$LDEV:exph.
:c.Logical output device
:c.:xph.HTML:pv.x:epv.:exph.  (e.g. HTML2, HTML3, HTML4)
:row.
:c.:xph.&amp.$OUT:exph.
:c.Output destination
:c.:xph.FILE:exph.
:row.
:c.:xph.&amp.$PDEV:exph.
:c.Physical output device
:c.:xph.HTML:pv.x:epv.:exph.  (e.g. HTML2, HTML3, HTML4)
:row refid=syssym temp.
:c.SCRIPT Command Options
:row.
:c.:xph.&amp.$ASCI:exph.
:c.ASCII output being generated
:c.0 (no) or 1 (yes)
:row.
:c.:xph.&amp.$DCF:exph.
:c.Current SCRIPT/VS (or in this case, &sysname.) release level
:c.&release.
:row.
:c.:xph.&amp.$INDX:exph.
:c.Index requested?
:c.0 (no) or 1 (yes)
:row.
:c.:xph.&amp.$LIB:exph.
:c.Macro library available
:c.0
:row.
:c.:xph.&amp.$PARM:exph.
:c.Command options
