.cp
:rev refid=r46.
:h2.&amp.Symbol value attributes
:erev refid=r46.
:p.These are the &amp.symbol value attributes supported by
&sysname..  For more information on their usage, see the
:cit.&script. User's Guide:ecit..
:table cols='8m *'
       align='c l'
       valign='t'
       split=yes.
:tcap.Supported &amp.symbol value attributes
:thd.
:c.Value Attribute
:c.Description
:ethd.
:row.
:c.:xph.&amp.E':exph.
:c.Verifies existence of a symbol.  Returns either a :q.1:eq. or
:q.0:eq. depending on whether or not the character string following
:xph.&amp.E':exph. is a defined symbol.
:row.
:c.:xph.&amp.L':exph.
:c.Determines the length of a symbol value or the number of
characters in any character string.
:row.
:c.:xph.&amp.T':exph.
:c.Analyzes the symbol type. Replaces the character string with
an :q.:xph.N:exph.:eq. if the value is numeric or null, or a
:q.:xph.C:exph.:eq. if the value contains nonnumeric data.
:row.
:c.:xph.&amp.U':exph.
:c.Converts lowercase characters to uppercase.
:row.
:c.:xph.&amp.V':exph.
:c.Returns the value of the symbol. Within &sysname.,
&amp.V'&amp.:pv.name:epv. is equivalent to &amp.:pv.name:epv..
:row.
:c.:xph.&amp.W':exph.
:c.Returns the width of a character string. Within &sysname.,
&amp.W'&amp.:pv.name:epv. is equivalent to &amp.L'&amp.:pv.name:epv..
:rev refid=r46.
:row.
:c.:xph.&amp.X':exph.
:c.Converts a hexadecimal notation (may be the value of another symbol)
to a character string :hp1.using the character coding of the platform
on which &sysname. is currently running:ehp1. (ASCII if running on a PC,
EBCDIC if running on a mainframe).  The :xph.&amp.$ASCI:exph. symbol
is set to 1 (one) if running on an ASCII platform,
otherwise the symbol is set to 0 (zero).
:erev refid=r46.
:etable.
.*-----
.cp
:rev refid=r42.
:h2.&script. control words
:erev refid=r42.
:table id=tsc refid=tsup4.
:tcap.Supported &script. control words
:tdesc.
The :q.How?:eq. column contains an :q.S:eq. if the control word is
supported via a Symbol table definition or an :q.I:eq. if the
control word is supported via a &sysname. internal routine.
:etdesc.
:thd.
:c.Control Word
:c.How?
:c.Comments
:rev refid=r42.
:c.Related &sysname. options
:erev refid=r42.
:ethd.
:row.:c.&period.&period.&period.:pv.label:epv.:c.I
:c.Both with and without a blank prior to the label name
:row.:c.&period.AN:c.I
:rev refid=r45.
:row.:c.&period.BF:c.I
:c.Begins the specified font.
:c.:spotref refid=fontag2.
:erev refid=r45.
:row.:c.&period.BL:c.S
:c.Mapped to new-paragraph.  When :xph.SOURCE=SCRIPT:exph., a
:xph.&period.BL:exph. is automatically generated and executed
whenever a blank line is processed.
:row.:c.&period.BR:c.S
:c.Mapped to new-line
:row.:c.&period.BX:c.S
:c.Mapped to a horizontal-rule
:row.:c.&period.CB:c.S
:c.Mapped to new-paragraph
:row.:c.&period.CE:c.I
:c.Text is centered either by using monospaced leading
blanks:fnref refid=fnline. or by using the &html
:xph.&lt.CENTER&gt.:exph. tag. The :spotref refid=centert.
specifies which technique is used.
:rev refid=r42.
:c.:spotref refid=center2. and
:spotref refid=linewi2.
:erev refid=r42.
:row.:c.&period.CP:c.S
:c.Mapped to new-paragraph
:row.:c.&period.CS:c.I
:c.
:row.:c.&period.CT:c.S
:c.Text included as-is.
:rev refid=r45.
:row.:c.&period.DC:c.I
:c.Only the :xph.CW:exph. and :xph.GML:exph. operands are supported.
For :xph.GML:exph., if less than two values are specified or if
:q.:xph.OFF:exph.:eq. is specified for either of the first two
values, error message 456 is issued and the control word is ignored.
:erev refid=r45.
:row.:c.&period.DD:c.I
:c.The :xph.LIB:exph. operand (whether explicitly specified or
defaulted) is supported on all platforms.  On MVS, the
:xph.DD:exph. and :xph.DSN:exph. operands are also supported.
If the :xph.TERM:exph. operand is specified, the entire control word
is ignored.
:row.:c.&period.DM:c.I
:c.Only the following two formats are supported:
:xmp.
  &period.dm name /stmt1/stmt2/ ... /stmtx&lbrk./&rbrk.
 
  &period.dm name on
  stmt1
  stmt2
   ....
  stmtx
  &period.dm off
:exmp.
:p.Parameters on the macro (e.g. ".name parm1 parm2") and
referencing them within the macro
(e.g. &amp.*, &amp.*0, &amp.*1, &amp.*2 ...) is also supported.
:row.:c.&period.DV:c.I
:row.:c.&period.EF:c.I
:rev refid=r44.
:c.The :xph.CLOSE:exph. option is supported.
:erev refid=r44.
:row.:c.&period.EL:c.I
:row.:c.&period.FN:c.I
:c.:xph..FN ON:exph. mapped to :xph.&colon.FN.:exph.,
:xph..FN OFF:exph. mapped to :xph.&colon.EFN.:exph..
:xph..FN&rbl.LEADER:exph. places 16 dashes on a separate line
.* :p.Not supported if :xph.SOURCE=SCRIPTONLY:exph.
:row.:c.&period.FO:c.I
:c.:xph..FO OFF:exph. mapped to &pre
.br;:xph..FO ON:exph. mapped to &epre
.br;:xph..FO CENTER:exph. is handled according to the
:spotref refid=centert.
.br;:xph..FO LEFT:exph. and :xph..FO RIGHT:exph. :q.terminate:eq. a
previous :xph..FO:exph. control word
.br;all other operands are ignored.
:rev refid=r42.
:c.:spotref refid=center2.
:erev refid=r42.
:row.:c.&period.GO:c.I
:c.Branching only to a label :hp1.later:ehp1. in the
file is supported.
:q.:xph.&period.GO:exph.:eq. control words branching to a label
:hp1.earlier:ehp1. in the file are ignored.
See additional comments in :hdref refid=caveat..
:p.The alternate formats
:q.:xph.&period.GOTO:exph.&rbl.:pv.label:epv.:eq. and
:q.:xph.&period.GO&rbl.TO:exph.&rbl.:pv.label:epv.:eq.
are also recognized.
:row.:c.&period.H0, &period.H1, &period.H2, &period.H3, &period.H4,
&period.H5 and &period.H6:c.I
:c.Mapped to their GML equivalent (&colon.H:pv.x:epv..).
:row.:c.&period.IF:c.I
