:rev refid=r42.
:h1 id=b2hvars.&amp.Symbols pre-defined by &sysname
:erev refid=r42.
:p.In addition to the normal &amp.symbols provided by Script/VS, GML
and &bm., &sysname. also provides a number of special-use
&amp.symbols. These are most often used within header and footer
files and in conjunction with certain options, such as
:rev refid=r42.
:xph.SPLITLINK.:pv.x:epv.=:exph.
:erev refid=r42.
and :xph.COMMENT=:exph..
:table cols='* 5*' align=l.
:thd.
:c.&amp.symbol
:c.Contains
:ethd.
:row. :c.&amp.b2hcoprext
:c.Text specified for the :xph.&colon.COPREXT:exph. tag (if any)
:row. :c.&amp.b2hcopyr
:c.Text specified for the :xph.COPYR=:exph. attribute (if any) on
the :xph.&colon.GDOC:exph. or :xph.&colon.USERDOC:exph. tag
:row. :c.&amp.b2hhead:pv.num:epv.
:c.Contains the header text of the most-recent
:xph.&colon.H:pv.num:epv..:exph. tag. The text specified for the
most-recent :xph.&colon.H0.:exph. is stored in
:xph.&amp.b2hhead0:exph., :xph.&colon.H1.:exph. is in
:xph.&amp.b2hhead1:exph., etc.
:p.When an :xph.&colon.H:pv.x:epv..:exph. tag is encountered, all
:q.lower:eq. symbols are cleared. For example, if an
:xph.&colon.H2.:exph. tag is encountered, the
:xph.&amp.b2hhead3:exph. symbol is cleared, :xph.&amp.b2hhead4:exph.
is cleared, :xph.&amp.b2hhead5:exph. is cleared, etc.
:row. :c.&amp.b2hhtml
:c.The &html. release level being generated as specified by the
:spotref refid=html2. option. Contains the number 2, 3
:rev refid=r42.
or 4.
:row. :c.&amp.b2hhtmlid
:c.The appropriate value of the :spotref refid=htmldo2.
option for the &html. release being generated.
:erev refid=R42.
:row. :c.&amp.b2hiall
:c.The fully-qualified name of the input file
:xmp.
  AIX:   /path/subdir/hh1.h2.hhh3
  CMS:   fn ft fm
  LINUX: /path/subdir/hh1.h2.hhh3
  MVS:   :pv.userid:epv..h1.h2.h3   &cont.
:pv.userid:epv..h1.h2.h3(member)
  OS/2:  c:\dir\subdir\fname.ext
  WIN95: c:\dir\subdir\fname.ext
  WINNT: c:\dir\subdir\fname.ext
:rev refid=r47.
  UNIX:  /path/subdir/hh1.h2.hhh3
:erev refid=r47.
:exmp.
:row. :c.&amp.b2hibmcopyr
:c.Text specified for the :xph.IBMCOPYR=:exph. attribute (if any) on
the :xph.&colon.USERDOC:exph. tag
:row. :c.&amp.b2hipath
:c.The path of the input file (if appropriate)
:xmp.
  AIX:   /path/subdir/
  CMS:   (Null string)
  LINUX: /path/subdir/
  MVS:   (Null string)
  OS/2:  c:\dir\subdir\
  WIN95: c:\dir\subdir\
  WINNT: c:\dir\subdir\
:rev refid=r47.
  UNIX:  /path/subdir/
:erev refid=r47.
:exmp.
:row. :c.&amp.b2hifile
:c.The non-path portion of the input file
:xmp.
  AIX:   hh1.h2.hhh3
  CMS:   fn ft
  LINUX: hh1.h2.hhh3
  MVS:   :pv.userid:epv..h1.h2.h3   &cont.
:pv.userid:epv..h1.h2.h3(member)
  OS/2:  fname.ext
  WIN95: fname.ext
  WINNT: fname.ext
:rev refid=r47.
  UNIX:  hh1.h2.hhh3
:erev refid=r47.
:exmp.
:row. :c.&amp.b2hidate
:c.The input file's date stamp in :pv.yyyy-mm-dd:epv. format
:row. :c.&amp.b2hitime
:c.The input file's time stamp in :pv.hh&colon.mm&colon.ss:epv. format
:row. :c.&amp.b2holall
:c.The fully-qualified name of the :hp1.logical:ehp1. output file
:xmp.
  AIX:   /path/subdir/hh1.h2.hhh3
  CMS:   fn ft fm
  LINUX: /path/subdir/hh1.h2.hhh3
  MVS:   :pv.userid:epv..h1.h2.h3
