:row. :c.&amp.b2hparttop
:c.The applicable next/prev links for the :hp1.top:ehp1. of an
&html. output file.  Normally referenced inside a user header file.
If the output file is :hp1.not:ehp1. being split, this is a null
string.  Otherwise, this contains either the value of
:rev refid=r42.
:xph.SPLITLINK.1,
SPLITLINK.3, SPLITLINK.5, SPLITLINK.11, SPLITLINK.13:exph. or
:xph.SPLITLINK.15:exph.,
:erev refid=r42.
depending on the circumstances.
:row. :c.&amp.b2hpartbot
:c.The applicable next/prev links for the :hp1.bottom:ehp1. of an
&html output file.  Normally referenced inside a user footer file.
If the output file is :hp1.not:ehp1. being split, this is a null
string.  Otherwise, this contains either the value of
:rev refid=r42.
:xph.SPLITLINK.2,
SPLITLINK.4, SPLITLINK.6, SPLITLINK.12, SPLITLINK.14:exph. or
:xph.SPLITLINK.16:exph.,
:erev refid=r42.
depending on the circumstances.
:row. :c.&amp.b2hplat
:c.A string containing both the platform on which &sysname. was run
and the destination platform with a dash separating the two.  If the
current platform and the destination platform are the same, then the
string contains only a single value.
:row. :c.&amp.b2hplatc
:c.The name of the :hp1.current:ehp1. platform on which &sysname. is
running, e.g. AIX, CMS, HPFS, Linux, MVS, OS2, WIN95, WINNT,
:rev refid=r47.
UNIX
:erev refid=r47.
:row. :c.&amp.b2hplatd
:c.The name of the :hp1.destination:ehp1. platform, as specified by
the :xph.DESTSYS=:exph. option
:row. :c.&amp.b2hrevchar
:c.Contains the revision character identifying the
:xph.&period.rc:exph. control word or :xph.&colon.revision:exph. tag
currently in effect (if any) -- intended for use in conjunction with
the :spotref refid=revtag.
:row. :c.&amp.b2hsig
:c.The name, release number and internal level of the &sysname.
program itself
:row. :c.&amp.b2huser
:c.The user ID executing the &sysname. program.
:xmp.
  AIX:   (Null string)
  CMS:   BY :pv.userid:epv. AT :pv.node:epv.
  LINUX: (Null string)
  MVS:   BY :pv.userid:epv. AT :pv.node:epv.
  OS/2:  (Null string)
  WIN95: (Null string)
  WINNT: (Null string)
:rev refid=r47.
  UNIX:  (Null string)
:erev refid=r47.
:exmp.
:tnote.
The following &amp.symbols are specifically intended to be
referenced within a
:rev refid=r42.
:xph.SPLITLINK.:pv.x:epv.=:exph.
:erev refid=r42.
option, but can be used anywhere.
:etnote.
:row. :c.&amp.b2hbot
:c.&html. label for the bottom of the current &html. file
:row. :c.&amp.b2hidx
:c.&html. file/label for the start of the index (if generated)
:row. :c.&amp.b2hnext
:c.&html. file/label for the next &html. file
:row. :c.&amp.b2hprev
:c.&html. file/label for the previous &html. file
:row. :c.&amp.b2hptoc
:c.&html. file/label for the start of the most-recent
Partial Table-of-Contents (PTOC).  Equivalent to &amp.b2htoc if no
PTOC yet encountered.
:row. :c.&amp.b2hthis
:c.Name of the current &html. file
:row. :c.&amp.b2htoc
:c.&html. file/label for the start of the Table-of-Contents
:row. :c.&amp.b2htop
:c.&html. label for the top of the current &html. file
:etable.
