.*---------- Summary of what's changed ----------
:h1 id=soar.&sysname. release history
:p.For detailed release information, including fixes, see the
:xph.B2H&rbl.NEWS:exph. file included with the &sysname. package.
.*----------
:rev refid=r47.
:h2 id=soar47.Updates for &sysname. Release 4.7
.*---
:p.:hp2.New or enhanced support of &bm./GML/Script markup&colon.:ehp2.
:ul compact.
:li.None
:eul.
.*---
:p.:hp2.&sysname.-specific updates&colon.:ehp2.
:ul compact.
:li.&sysname. will now run under Regina Rexx (Release 3.0 or higher).
Regina is a free Rexx implementation which can be used as an
alternative to IBM's Object Rexx and is available at
.website regina-rexx.sourceforge.net/
:li.&sysname. will now support and run in Unix when run under Regina Rexx
:li.Multiple lines generated by
:q.:xph..sk:exph.:eq. or :q.:xph..sp:exph.:eq. are being ignored by
modern web browsers due to their suppressing multiple blank lines.
Output created by &sysname. altered to prevent this suppression.
:li.When run on Windows or OS/2, a filename enclosed in double-quote
characters is now accepted on the command line.  This to ensure
consistency with other filename handling routines in Windows and OS/2.
:li.Additional &html. tags can now be customized.
The :xph.HTMLATT=:exph. option was enhanced to support customization
of the :xph.&lt.A&gt.:exph., :xph.&lt.DD&gt.:exph., :xph.&lt.DT&gt.:exph.,
:xph.&lt.FORM&gt.:exph., :xph.&lt.IMG&gt.:exph.
and :xph.&lt.INPUT&gt.:exph. &html. tags.
(see the :spotref refid=htmlatt.)
:eul.
.*---
:p.:hp2.New or updated &sysname. options&colon.:ehp2.
(For information on all &sysname. options, see :hdref refid=cmdparm.)
:xmp.
  HTMLATT.:pv.tagname:epv.=':pv.text:epv.'              (more :pv.tagname:epv. values)
:exmp.
.*---
:p.:hp2.Updates to the User's Guide&colon.:ehp2.
:ul compact.
:li.Section added regarding the REXX versions under which B2H will run
:li.Many updates to reflect the UNIX platform
:eul.
.*---
:p.:hp2.System profile updates&colon.:ehp2.
:ul compact.
:li.Various default definitions added for UNIX support
:eul.
.*---
:p.:hp2.System symbol table updates&colon.:ehp2.
:ul compact.
:li.Definition for :q.:xph..sk:exph.:eq. and :q.:xph..sp:exph.:eq.
:eul.
:erev refid=r47.
.*----------
:rev refid=r46.
:h2 id=soar46.Updates for &sysname. Release 4.6
.*---
:p.:hp2.New or enhanced support of &bm./GML/Script markup&colon.:ehp2.
:ul.
:li.Support :xph.&amp.X':pv.hhhh:epv.:exph.
symbol value attribute (convert hex characters)
:li.Additional DCF symbols defined to more
closely emulate the mainframe environment (see :hdref refid=syssym.)
:li.:q.:xph.ON/OFF:exph.:eq. option of the :q.:xph..rc:exph.:eq.
control word now supported
.br;(e.g. :q.:xph..rc 1 on/off:exph.:eq.)
:li.:xph.FRAME=RULES:exph. now recognized and supported on
the :xph.&colon.FIG:exph. tag
:eul.
.*---
:p.:hp2.&sysname.-specific updates&colon.:ehp2.
:ul.
:li.Tag delimiter character(s) may be changed using the
:xph..DC:exph. control word. Tag delimiters can even be
turned off (:xph..DC GML OFF:exph.)
:li.If :xph.&colon.TDESC:exph. is encountered in a table, but not ended
using :xph.&colon.ETDESC:exph., the :xph.&colon.ETABLE:exph. tag will
end the :xph.&colon.TDESC:exph..  (the :xph.&colon.ETDESC:exph. tag
is not required in all :q.flavors:eq. of GML/Bookmaster.)
:li.If :xph.&colon.ADDRESS:exph. is encountered, but not ended using
:xph.&colon.EADDRESS:exph., either the :xph.&colon.ETITLE:exph.
or :xph.&colon.ETITLEP:exph. tag will end the :xph.&colon.ADDRESS:exph..
If neither :xph.&colon.ETITLE:exph. or :xph.&colon.ETITLEP:exph.
is encountered, a "missing &colon.EADDRESS" message is issued.
:eul.
.*---
:p.:hp2.New or updated &sysname. options&colon.:ehp2.
(For information on all &sysname. options, see :hdref refid=cmdparm.)
:xmp.
  BORDERTAG=':pv.tag:epv.'                          (new option)
  BORDERTAG.:pv.x:epv.=':pv.tag:epv.'                        (new option)
  HRTAG.:pv.x:epv.=':pv.tag:epv.'                            (HRTAG.4 now used)
:exmp.
.*---
:p.:hp2.Updates to the User's Guide&colon.:ehp2.
:ul compact.
:li.New appendix section documenting supporting system-type
&amp.symbols (e.g. :xph.&amp.SYSYEAR:exph., :xph.&amp.$INDX:exph.,
:xph.&amp.$PDEV:exph.). See :hdref refid=syssym..
:eul.
.*---
:p.:hp2.System profile updates&colon.:ehp2.
:ul compact.
:li.None
:eul.
.*---
:p.:hp2.System symbol table updates&colon.:ehp2.
:ul compact.
:li.None
:eul.
:erev refid=r46.
.*----------
:rev refid=r45.
:h2 id=soar45.Updates for &sysname. Release 4.5
.*---
:p.:hp2.New or enhanced support of &bm./GML/Script markup&colon.:ehp2.
:ul.
:li.:xph.&period.DC:exph. control word with :xph.CW:exph. and
:xph.GML:exph. options now supported
:li.:xph.&period.BF:exph., :xph.&period.PF:exph. and
:xph.&period.PI:exph. control words are now supported
:li.Multiple :xph.&colon.AUTHOR:exph. tags now supported
:eul.
.*---
:p.:hp2.&sysname.-specific updates&colon.:ehp2.
:ul.
:li.The parser has been updated which allows the following enhancements:
:ul compact.
:li.:q.Splitting:eq. of the output &html. is now supported for
:xph.SOURCE=SCRIPTONLY:exph.
:li.:xph.When SOURCE=SCRIPTONLY:exph., all control words
:hp1.mapped:ehp1. to &bm./GML tags are now supported.
Prior to R4.5, control words that were normally handled by simply
:hp1.mapping:ehp1. them to their &bm./GML equivalent
(e.g. :xph..FN:exph. to :xph.&colon.FN.:exph.,
:xph..H:pv.x:epv.:exph. to :xph.&colon.H:pv.x:epv..:exph.)
were not supported when :xph.SOURCE=SCRIPTONLY:exph..
:li.Tag delimiter character(s) may be changed using the
:xph.&period.DC:exph. control word
:eul.
:li.Symbol table records can now be imbedded within the source document
using the new :q.:xph..*B2H SYMBOL:exph.:eq. statement
:li.Improved support for character set translations:
:ul compact.
:li.New :xph.&colon.XLATEO.:exph. symbol table statement allows
translations specific to :hp1.output:ehp1. &html. records
:li.:xph.&colon.XLATEI.:exph. symbol table statement
(was :xph.&colon.XLATE.:exph.) allows translations specific
to :hp1.input:ehp1. source records
:li.Improved handling of :xph..TI:exph. and :xph..TR:exph.
:eul.
:li.New :xph.LINENUM=:exph. option allows &sysname. to recognize
and ignore line numbers in source records
:li.A label cell is no longer generated for
:xph.&colon.SYNTAX&rbl.STYLE=LBLBOX:exph. if no label data has been
provided
:li.Empty syntax diagrams are now suppressed
:li.If a :xph.&period.RE:exph. (restore environment) control word
changes the pre-formatting status of the output, the appropriate
&html. tags are now generated to automatically compensate
:li.The :xph.DLFMT=:exph. and :xph.GLFMT=:exph. options now default
to :xph.TABLE:exph. if generating &html. 3 (or higher);
if generating &html. 2, both default to :xph.DL:exph.
:li.Additional diagnostics provided for I/O and allocation errors
under MVS
:li.To show a vertical bar, such as those used for syntax diagrams
and the :xph.&colon.SCREEN:exph. tag, &sysname. now generates
:q.:xph.&amp.#124;:exph.:eq. instead of a physical vertical bar.
(This circumvents a problem experienced by some users where their
upload/download process was translating a vertical bar into something else.)
:li.In a profile file, comments may now be placed after any option(s)
by preceding the comment with two dashes (:xph.--:exph.).
This capability was already available for the symbol table file.
:li.Indentation of multi-line messages within the &sysname.
log was changed to improve readability
:eul.
.*---
:p.:hp2.New or updated &sysname. options&colon.:ehp2.
(For information on all &sysname. options, see :hdref refid=cmdparm.)
:xmp.
  DEFTEXT.:pv.name:epv.=':pv.text:epv.'                           (new names)
  FONTTAG=':pv.fonttext:epv.,:pv.efonttext:epv.,&cont.
&lbrk.PROP|NOPROP&rbrk.'&cont.
    (new option)
  H3ADDONS=&lbrc. NO | YES &rbrc.                         (removed - obsolete)
  H3TABLE=&lbrc. COMPLEX | SIMPLE &rbrc.                  (removed - obsolete)
  INDEXREFLINK=&lbrc. :pk def.NO:epk. | YES &rbrc.                     (new option)
  LINENUM=&lbrc. :pk def.NO:epk. | BEGIN | END | &cont.
:pv.scol:epv.-:pv.ecol:epv. &rbrc.      (new option)
  PROCACT='...'                                 (additional operand)
:exmp.
.*---
:p.:hp2.Updates to the User's Guide&colon.:ehp2.
:ul compact.
:li.Section added on how to use only Script/VS control words to
include/exclude text when converting to &html.
:li.:hdref refid=faqh13., :hdref refid=faqh14. and :hdref refid=faqh15.
added to Frequently-Asked-Questions section
:li.Document new message numbers 109, 152, 317 and 318
:li.Miscellaneous updates to reflect R4.5 changes
:rev refid=r46.
:li.New appendix section documenting supporting system-type
&amp.symbols (see :hdref refid=syssym.)
:erev refid=r46.
:eul.
.*---
:p.:hp2.System profile updates&colon.:ehp2.
:ul compact.
:li.Show defaults for new options
:li.Change vertical bars to "&amp.#124;"
:eul.
.*---
:p.:hp2.System symbol table updates&colon.:ehp2.
:ul compact.
:li.:xph.&colon.XLATE.:exph. statement renamed to :xph.&colon.XLATEI.:exph.
(:xph.&colon.XLATE.:exph. still supported, but :xph.&colon.XLATEI.:exph.
preferred)
:li.:xph.&period.SD:exph. Script/VS control word defined as being
ignored
:li.Change definition of :xph.&period.BF:exph., :xph.&period.DC:exph.,
:xph.&period.PF:exph. and :xph.&period.PI:exph. from ignored to
handled internally
:eul.
:erev refid=r45.
.*----------
:rev refid=r44.
:h2 id=soar44.Updates for &sysname. Release 4.4
.*---
:p.:hp2.New or enhanced support of &bm./GML/Script markup&colon.:ehp2.
:ul.
:li.:xph.&period.LP:exph. now properly left-aligned when within a
:xph.&colon.DL:exph. or :xph.&colon.GL:exph. and a table is being
generated (e.g. :xph.DLFMT=TABLE:exph. or :xph.GLFMT=TABLE:exph.)
:li.:xph.&period.EF:exph. now fully supported with or without
the :xph.CLOSE:exph. operand.
:li.Script/VS :xph.&amp.$CONT.:exph. and :xph.&amp.$TAB.:exph.
symbols now supported
:eul.
.*---
:p.:hp2.&sysname.-specific updates&colon.:ehp2.
:ul.
:li.When &sysname. is run on MVS, if the physical output file is
DSORG=PS and is also pre-allocated, &sysname. will no longer delete
and reallocate it, improving efficiency
:eul.
.*---
:p.:hp2.New or updated &sysname. options&colon.:ehp2.
(For information on all &sysname. options, see :hdref refid=cmdparm.)
:ul.
:li.When &sysname. is run on MVS (OS/390), the :xph.HEADER=:exph.
and :xph.FOOTER=:exph.  options now support specifying the input
file using the ":xph.DD&colon.:pv.ddname:epv.:exph." syntax
:eul.
.*---
:p.:hp2.Updates to the User's Guide&colon.:ehp2.
:ul compact.
:li.Minor updates to reflect R4.4 changes
:eul.
.*---
:p.:hp2.System profile updates&colon.:ehp2.
:ul compact.
:li.None
:eul.
.*---
:p.:hp2.System symbol table updates&colon.:ehp2.
:ul compact.
:li.:xph.&colon.COVER:exph. definition updated to correct
:q.missing period:eq. error messages
:li.:xph.&amp.divide:exph. symbol added in addition to
:xph.&amp.divid:exph.
:li.:xph.&amp.florin:exph. symbol added and mapped to
:xph.&amp.#402;:exph.
:eul.
:erev refid=r44.
