:rev refid=r43.
:h2 id=soar43.Updates for &sysname. Release 4.3
.*---
:p.:hp2.New or enhanced support of &bm./GML/Script markup&colon.:ehp2.
:ul.
:li.If an :xph.&colon.ADDRESS:exph. tag is encountered within
:xph.&colon.PROLOG/&colon.EPROLOG:exph., hold the text until
the formal title page is generated; otherwise display the address
text as encountered.
:li.:xph.&colon.COVER:exph. now treated as a synonym of
:xph.&colon.TIPAGE:exph.; both tags now generate a formal title page
:eul.
.*---
:p.:hp2.&sysname.-specific updates&colon.:ehp2.
:ul.
:li.:xph.LOG=:exph. option now accepts an asterisk (*),
which is dynamically replaced by the input filename.
For more information, see the :spotref refid=logopt..
:li.When running as a Pipeline filter, &sysname. now supports
writing log records to a pipeline output stream
:eul.
.*---
:p.:hp2.New or updated &sysname. options&colon.:ehp2.
(For information on all &sysname. options, see :hdref refid=cmdparm.)
:ul.
:li.New :xph.LOG=:exph. capabilities as mentioned above
:eul.
.*---
:p.:hp2.Updates to the User's Guide&colon.:ehp2.
:ul compact.
:li.Describe new B2H128 message
:li.Minor updates to reflect R4.3 changes
:eul.
.*---
:p.:hp2.System profile updates&colon.:ehp2.
:ul compact.
:li.None
:eul.
.*---
:p.:hp2.System symbol table updates&colon.:ehp2.
:ul compact.
:li.Change definition of :xph.&amp.OELIG:exph. to
:xph.&amp.OElig:exph.
:li.Defined :xph.&colon.ETOC:exph. and :xph.&colon.EDOCPROF:exph.
as ignored tags
:li.Recognize :xph.&amp.$RB.:exph. as meaning a blank
:li.Define :xph.&colon.COVER:exph.,
:xph.&colon.PROLOG/&colon.EPROLOG:exph. as internal tags
:eul.
:erev refid=r43.
.*----------
:rev refid=r42.
:h2 id=soar42.Updates for &sysname. Release 4.2
.*---
:p.:hp2.New or enhanced support of &bm./GML/Script markup&colon.:ehp2.
:ul.
:li.:xph.&colon.CGDEF:exph. and :xph.&colon.XMPDEF:exph. tags
now supported
:li.:xph.APPHD1=:exph., :xph.APPHD1X=:exph. and :xph.DIALOG=:exph.
attributes now supported on the :xph.&colon.DOCPROF:exph. tag
:li.:xph.SCALE=:exph. attribute now supported on the following tags:
:xph.&colon.CGRAPHIC:exph., :xph.&colon.CODEL:exph.,
:xph.&colon.DIALOG:exph., :xph.&colon.DIRECT:exph.,
:xph.&colon.FIG:exph., :xph.&colon.MSGL:exph.,
:xph.&colon.SCHDATE:exph., :xph.&colon.SCREEN:exph.,
:xph.&colon.SYNTAX:exph., :xph.&colon.TABDATA:exph.,
:xph.&colon.TABLE:exph. and :xph.&colon.XMP:exph.
:li.:xph.TEXT=:exph. attribute now supported on the
:xph.&colon.AUTHOR:exph. tag
:li.:xph.LEVEL=:exph. attribute now supported on the
:xph.&colon.DOCNUM:exph. tag
:li.Within a table, when too many :xph.&colon.C:exph. tags are
encountered for a logical row, a :xph.&colon.ROW:exph. tag is
automatically inserted to force a new row
:li.The IBM-internal :xph.CAPBC=:exph., :xph.EQBC=:exph. and
:xph.FNBC=:exph. attributes on the :xph.&colon.DOCPROF:exph. tag
no longer cause a warning message to be issued
:li.The IBM-internal :xph.&colon.DFREF:exph. tag no longer causes
a warning message to be issued
:eul.
.*---
:p.:hp2.&sysname.-specific updates&colon.:ehp2.
:ul.
:li.&html. 4 output can now be specified (see :hdref refid=faqh4.)
:li.Layout of formal title page now corresponds more closely
to the &bm. standard
:li.Appearance of :xph.&colon.H5:exph. though :xph.&colon.H20:exph.
now corresponds more closely to the &bm.'s default layout
(see new :xph.HTAG=:exph. option)
:li.Propagation of font color changes used with
:xph.&period.RC/&colon.REV/&colon.EREV:exph.
can be enabled/disabled on a per-revision code basis
:li.Footnote appearance can now be customized using the new
:xph.FNTAG=:exph. option.
(Thanks to Mark Gaubatz for his code update that led to this
enhancement!) Default footnote id now displayed as a superscript
instead of normal text enclosed in parentheses.
:li.Improved &html. output for &bm. tables which
use :xph.ARRANGE=:exph.
:li.Improved &html. output for &bm.'s Messages and Codes tags
:li.Improved &html. output for &bm.'s Dialog tags
:li.Improved appearance and customization capability
for syntax diagrams (see item :hdref refid=faqsn.)
:li.The ability to selectively process profile records, symbol table
records and :q.:xph.&period.*&sysname.:exph.:eq. statements has been
enhanced by allowing the &html. release level being generated to
also be a selection criteria
:li.The new :q.:xph.SETUPTAG.:pv.tagname:epv.=:exph.:eq. option
allows you to define &html. statements to precede/follow the output
generated for a particular GML/&bm. tag.  For example, you could
specify that a certain font be loaded specifically for
:xph.&colon.CGRAPHIC.:exph. diagrams or cause the entire title page
to be centered or right-justified.
:li.New :q.:xph.HTMLDOCID.:pv.rel:epv.=:exph.:eq. option allows you
to explicitly specify the Document Type Definition value for the
first record of the &html. output -- the :q.:pv.xxx:epv.:eq. in the
following:
:xmp.  &lt.!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//IETF//DTD HTML &cont.
:pv.xxx:epv.//EN"&gt.:exmp.
:p.The new :xph.&amp.b2hhtmlid:exph. symbol is defined to contain
the appropriate value of this option for the &html. release being
generated.
:li.Additional process names :q.:xph.HTML2+:exph.:eq.,
:q.:xph.HTML3+:exph.:eq. and :q.:xph.HTML4+:exph.:eq. for use with
:xph.&colon.PSC:exph. allow more generalized selection of text
:li.New :q.:xph.&period.*B2H MSG:exph.:eq. statement added to allow
messages to be issued (and the return code set) from within the
document.  Can also be returned from a user program to show messages
and set return codes.
:li.New :q.:xph.HEADREC=:exph.:eq. option provides the ability to
insert records into the header section of the output &html. file.
Most commonly used to include JavaScript code.
:li.All options, statements and text regarding :q.splitting:eq. of
the output &html. file have been renamed for consistency.  The use
of :q.BREAK:eq. and :q.PART:eq. have been changed to :q.SPLIT:eq.:
:ul compact.
:li.:q.:xph.AUTOPART=:exph.:eq. is now :q.:xph.AUTOSPLIT=:exph.:eq.,
:li.:q.:xph.PARTDIGITS=:exph.:eq. is now :q.:xph.SPLITDIGITS=:exph.:eq.,
:li.:q.:xph.PARTDIR=:exph.:eq. is now :q.:xph.SPLITDIR=:exph.:eq.,
:li.:q.:xph.PARTLINK=:exph.:eq. is now :q.:xph.SPLITLINK=:exph.:eq. and
:li.:q.:xph.PARTNAMES=:exph.:eq. is now :q.:xph.SPLITNAMES=:exph.:eq.
:li.The :q.:xph..*B2H&rbl.BREAK:exph.:eq. statement is now
:q.:xph..*B2H&rbl.SPLIT:exph.:eq.
:eul.
For downward compatibility, all the old names are still recognized
as aliases of their new official names.
:li.Both the :q.:xph.SPLITDIR.x=:exph.:eq. and
:q.:xph.SPLITNAME.x=:exph.:eq. options now allow the
:q.:pv.x:epv.:eq. value to be specified as :q.:xph.NEXT:exph.:eq.,
which allows you to name the :hp1.next:ehp1. split file, wherever
and whenever it occurs.
:eul.
.*---
:p.:hp2.New or updated &sysname. options&colon.:ehp2.
(For information on all &sysname. options, see :hdref refid=cmdparm.)
:xmp.
  APPHD1=':pv.text:epv.'              &cont.
                       (new option)
  APPHD1X=':pv.text:epv.'             &cont.
                       (new option)
  AUTOSPLIT= ...             &cont.
                       (was "AUTOPART=")
  DEFTEXT.:pv.name:epv.=':pv.text:epv.'&cont.
                               (additional names)
  DEFTEXT.:pv.name:epv.=':pv.text:epv.',&cont.
&lbrk.:pv.width:epv.&rbrk.&cont.
                       (new operand)
  DIALOG='&lbrk.LABEL&rbrk. &lbrk.FONT&rbrk. &lbrk.COLOR&rbrk.'&cont.
                   (new option)
  DIALOGTAG.:pv.x:epv.=':pv.ts,te,fs,fe,cs,cs:epv.'&cont.
                   (new option)
  FNTAG=':pv.cs,ce,ls,le,lcs,lce,lts,lte,ts,te:epv.'&cont.
         (new option)
  HEADREC.:pv.num:epv.=':pv.text:epv.'         &cont.
                       (new option)
  HRTAG=':pv.text:epv.'               &cont.
                       (no :q.:pv.x:epv.:eq. required)
  HRTAG.:pv.x:epv.=':pv.text:epv.'             &cont.
                       (new :q.:pv.x:epv.:eq. values)
  HTAG=':pv.hs,he,ss,sr:epv.'         &cont.
                       (new option)
  HTAG.:pv.num:epv.=':pv.hs,he,ss,sr:epv.'     &cont.
                       (new option)
  HTML=&lbrc. 2 | 3 | 4 &rbrc.&cont.
                                (new operand)
  HTMLDOCID.:pv.htmlrel:epv.=':pv.text:epv.'&cont.
                          (new option)
  REVTAG=':pv.revtext:epv.,:pv.erevtext:epv.,&cont.
&lbrk.PROP|NOPROP&rbrk.'&cont.
           (new operand)
  SETUPTAG.:pv.tagname:epv.=':pv.beforetext:epv.',':pv.aftertext:epv.'&cont.
         (new option)
  SPLITDIGITS= ...           &cont.
                       (was "PARTDIGITS=")
  SPLITDIR= ...              &cont.
                       (was "PARTDIR=")
  SPLITDIR.NEXT= ...         &cont.
                       (new operand)
  SPLITLINK= ...             &cont.
                       (was "PARTLINK=")
  SPLITLINK.x= ...           &cont.
                       (was "PARTLINK.x=")
  SPLITNAME.x= ...           &cont.
                       (was "PARTNAME.x=")
  SPLITNAME.NEXT= ...        &cont.
                       (new operand)
  TOCTAG=':pv.ls,le,ie,ie,ts,te:epv.' &cont.
                       (new operands)
:exmp.
