.*----------
:h2 id=soar41.Updates for &sysname. Release 4.1
.*---
:p.:hp2.New or enhanced support of &bm./GML/Script markup&colon.:ehp2.
:ul.
:li.:xph.OLSEQ=:exph. attribute now supported on the
:xph.&colon.DOCPROF:exph. tag
:li.:q.:xph.&period.NF:exph.:eq. and :q.:xph.&period.PP:exph.:eq.
control words now supported
:eul.
.*---
:p.:hp2.&sysname.-specific updates&colon.:ehp2.
:ul.
:li.Year2000 support added
:li.B2H now executes on the LINUX platform
(you must have IBM's Object REXX for LINUX installed)
:li.Font color changes used with
:xph.&period.RC/&colon.REV/&colon.EREV:exph.
are now propagated into &html. 3 tables
:li.For ordered lists, &sysname. now generates the appropriate
:xph.&lt.OL TYPE=:pv.x:epv.&gt.:exph. tag to allow different
numbering schemes based on the :q.nesting:eq. of the list.  This
means the main list will be numbered, the first sub-list will have
alphabetic indices, and so on.  The :xph.OLSEQ=:exph. option (also
recognized on &bm.'s :xph.&colon.DOCPROF:exph. tag) can be used to
override this behavior.  The list item reference generated for
:xph.&colon.LIREF:exph. now reflects the actual indice.
:li.The :xph.SYNFONT=:exph. option now also affects how the
:xph.&colon.SYNNTREF:exph. tag is shown
:li.Support added for abbreviations of various tag attributes
(e.g. :q.:xph.COL:exph.:eq. for :q.:xph.COLS:exph.:eq.,
:q.:xph.RETCODE:exph.:eq. for :q.:xph.RETCODES:exph.:eq.)
:eul.
.*---
:p.:hp2.New or updated &sysname. options&colon.:ehp2.
(For information on all &sysname. options, see :hdref refid=cmdparm.)
:xmp.
  DESTSYS=&lbrc.AIX|HPFS|LINUX|MVS|OS2|VM|WIN95|WINNT&rbrc.   (new operand)
  LIREF=&lbrc. NO | ID | ACTUAL &rbrc.                        (new operand)
  OLSEQ=':pv.sequence codes:epv.'                            (new option)
:exmp.
.*---
:p.:hp2.Updates to the User's Guide&colon.:ehp2.
:ul compact.
:li.Document changes for R4.1
:eul.
.*---
:p.:hp2.System profile updates&colon.:ehp2.
:ul compact.
:li.Add LINUX-awareness
:li.Add default value for :xph.DEFTEXT.ARTLABEL=:exph.
:eul.
.*---
:p.:hp2.System symbol table updates&colon.:ehp2.
:ul compact.
:li.Define :q.:xph.&period.GOTO:exph.:eq. as a valid control word
:li.Define subscript symbols :xph.&amp.sub0-&amp.sub9:exph.
and superscript symbols :xph.&amp.sup0-&amp.subp:exph.
:li.Any text specified on the :xph.&colon.MINDEX:exph. tag now
totally ignored
:eul.
.*----------
:h2 id=soar40.Updates for &sysname. Release 4.0, 4.01 and 4.02
.*---
:p.:hp2.New or enhanced support of &bm./GML/Script markup&colon.:ehp2.
:ul.
:li.New &bm./GML tags now supported
:ul compact.
:li.(:hp1.R4.01:ehp1.)
Syntax :q.railroad:eq. diagrams now supported
(:xph.&colon.SYNTAX.:exph. family of tags)
:li.:xph.&colon.IBMLPS/&colon.EIBMLPS:exph. and
:xph.&colon.WARRANTY:exph. tags
for IBM-internal Licensed Program Specification documents
:li.:xph.&colon.LITDATA/&colon.ELITDATA:exph.
:li.:xph.&colon.PGMNUM:exph.
:eul.
:li.New &script. control words now supported
:ul compact.
:li.:xph.&period.AN:exph., :xph.&period.OR:exph. and
:xph.&period.DV:exph.
:li.:xph.&period.GO:exph. and :xph....:pv.label:epv.:exph.
(see :hdref refid=caveat. for restrictions).
:li.:xph.&period.SU ON:exph. and :xph.&period.SU OFF:exph.
:eul.
:li.Enhanced support for existing markup
:ul compact.
:li.:xph.&period.DD:exph. control word:
:xph.DD:exph. and :xph.DSN:exph. options supported
:li.:xph.&period.NAMEFILE:exph. macro:
:xph.TSOFULL=:exph. and :xph.TSOPART=:exph. attributes supported
:li.:q.:xph.SCALE=:exph.:eq. attribute on the :xph.&colon.XMP:exph.
tag is now supported
:li.The :q.:xph.&period.BL:exph.:eq. (Blank Line) control word is
now generated by &sysname. and executed whenever a blank line is
processed (unless a blank line is already significant, such as
within a :q.:xph.&colon.XMP/&colon.EXMP:exph.:eq.)
:li.The blank separating a &script. control word from the first
parameter is now optional (e.g. :q.:xph.&period.CP24:exph.:eq. and
:q.:xph.&period.CP 24:exph.:eq. are synonymous)
:li.:xph.&colon.PD:exph. no longer generates a new-paragraph before
the text
:eul.
:li.Support the &amp.$YEAR symbol (4-digit year) added to &bm
for Year2000 support
:eul.
.*---
:p.:hp2.&sysname.-specific updates&colon.:ehp2.
:ul.
:li.(:hp1.R4.01:ehp1.) Under MVS, the output file can now be
specified either by referencing the dataset name or by DD
:li.(:hp1.R4.01:ehp1.) If an error occurs while writing an output
file (e.g. output disk fills up), issue message B2H317 and stop
:li.MVS is now a supported platform
:li.Value of :xph.GMLTYPE=:exph. attribute on
:xph.&period.NAMEIT:exph. macro now validated.
Error message B2H458 issued if an invalid value is detected.
:li.When running on VM/CMS:
:ul compact.
:li.Default destination platform is now :q.:xph.VM:exph.:eq.
(was :q.:xph.OS2:exph.:eq.)
:li.Default value for :xph.HTMLEXT=:exph. and :xph.HTMPEXT=:exph.
options now :q.:xph.HTML:exph.:eq. (was :q.:xph.HTM:exph.:eq.)
:eul.
:li.The name :q.Advantis:eq. changed to :q.IBM Corporation:eq.
within all files of the package as Advantis is now a part of IBM
:li.:xph.CHARSET=:exph. option added to support coded character sets
associated with the generated &html. document
:eul.
.*---
